{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DH5ktzWiUGiya4sBhEZsTk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. Here's what was wrong and what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` Kubernetes TLS secret contained a certificate valid only from Jan 1–2, 2020 — deliberately expired. The `demo-ingress` resource was configured to use this secret for TLS termination of `demo.example.com`, causing all HTTPS connections to fail certificate validation.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Identified the CA key at `/tmp/test-ca.key` (the same CA whose cert is mounted into the `curl-test` pod at `/tmp/tls/ca.crt` via the `test-ca` ConfigMap)\n2. Generated a new 2048-bit RSA key and leaf certificate for `demo.example.com` with SAN, valid until June 2028, signed by that CA\n3. Replaced the secret: `kubectl apply` with the new cert/key over the existing `expired-tls-secret`\n4. Fixed the empty `INGRESS_NODE_IP` in `/tmp/ingress_env` (set to `172.18.0.6`, the node's internal IP)\n\ncurl now returns `hello` with exit code 0 and `SSL certificate verify ok`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":420,"cache_read_input_tokens":69138,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":420},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7cbf3f3a-0b20-4d44-96cd-b7167a7039e2","uuid":"156a60e7-2474-4b1f-92b4-20a50c8bcbae","request_id":"req_011CcaipRMdcmesDbABJXUDb"}
